1) What are the pillars of Wi-Fi security?

The main pillars of Wi-Fi security are:

| Pillar                       | Purpose                                     |
| ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| Authentication               | Verify identity of client/AP                |
| Confidentiality (Encryption) | Protect data from eavesdropping             |
| Integrity                    | Ensure packets are not modified             |


Authentication
It ensures only valid users/devices connect.
Examples:

* PSK authentication
* 802.1X/EAP authentication
* SAE in WPA3

Confidentiality (Encryption)

Encryption protects wireless traffic from attackers.
Examples:

* WEP
* TKIP
* CCMP (AES)
* GCMP

Integrity

Integrity ensures packets are not altered.

Mechanisms:

* MIC
* CBC-MAC
* Galois authentication

Protects against:

* Packet tampering
* Forged frames


